Package au.edu.anu.omhtk.collections

package au.edu.anu.omhtk.collections

Defines additional List types.

These classes are attempts to fix some issues with java lists:

  • Iterators resistant to a modification of the list while looping on it (avoiding the dreadful ConcurrentModificationException).
  • Iterator on a set of Lists (shallow merging, i.e. without copy of any list items).
Author:
Jacques Gignoux - 18 mai 2021
  • Class Summary
    Class
    Description
    DynamicList<T>
    Implementation of List<T> with a self-correcting iterator which allows removing of items while in a for loop on the list.
    ListNode<T>
    A container for items in a List (formerly AotList).
    QuickListOfLists<T>
    An immutable list of lists enabling iteration over the whole set as if it was a single list, with a minimal cost at creation time (hence the 'Quick').
